      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        50,
        50
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "=== ATTACK VECTOR: LLM01 Indirect Injection via Structured Data ===\n\nGUARDRAIL VARIANT\n\nAdded protection:\n- Code node: Data Boundary Wrapper wraps external ticket data in <external_data> XML delimiters and prepends an instruction for the agent to treat it as data-only.\n\nCompare results with wf_03_indirect_email_db_baseline.json.\n\nResearch questions:\n- Does XML boundary wrapping prevent instruction override from within external data?\n- Can injection payloads that include closing </external_data> tags bypass the wrapper?\n- Does the explicit instruction \"treat as data only\" reduce agent susceptibility?",
        "height": 300,
        "width": 450
      }
    }
